{
  "stem": "15943.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My Uncle Baruch, my mother's favorite brother, my favorite uncle, he had a coat, a great-- great tweed coat that had a-- a fur inside.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this-- the fur we had to take out and give it to the Nazis because they took everything that had fur.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my mother took out the fur from inside that-- didn't give up the whole coat-- and gave the fur away.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the coat was hanging there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I adopted my brothers, I lost the legal right as a child.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were getting some clothes from social services.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So because we had no-- things were falling apart-- and I didn't have much.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they felt so bad that, you know, Mommy would be unhappy to look-- the schmattas that you're wearing, that you're not dressed properly.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what they did, they [SIGHS] took the bread to a tailor, a uncle of a friend of mine, and took the coat that was hanging by us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they told him to take the inside of the coat, where the fabric still looked fresh, and make a suit for me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was the suit that I came to Auschwitz, wearing at Auschwitz, going to suit.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You were still in the ghetto when they made the suit?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I was still in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother was very close to that uncle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was-- was a rich family life between her sisters, one sister, and this brother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "His name was [YIDDISH], and Uncle Baruch, her brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then she had two brothers that died, I think '36.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I remember, I wrote down the dates, before the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They both had cancer.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But she was close with her sister-in-laws and with the children.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
